            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> You can always override the hover handler and disable wrapping with its configuration argument. [The docs show how to do this](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.handlers.hover()).\n\nIf I add `wrap = false`, then the window is too small for the text and it gets cut by it, i.e. in order to see the end of the sentence I must enter the window and scroll horizontally. Does this confirm it's an LSP issue and not a neovim one?",
